CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 9, reads: "Fire Local - Volunteer fire rescuers backed an ice cream truck against this store then climbed on top of it. Because second-floor windows were still too high, rescuers had to work 'piggy back' and allow youngsters to slide down two human ladders to ice cream truck and then jump to ground. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire damaged three story brick building with Royal Food Market at street level, Pennsylvania Avenue at Fulton Street, Northside
